article_title: MetroWest Free Medical Program still providing care after 11 years
article_text:
By Brad Avery/Daily News Staff

Posted Nov. 1, 2015 at 11:33 AM

Updated Nov 2, 2015 at 2:18 PM

article_metadata.description: SUDBURY - It's Tuesday night at Congregation Beth-El and the worship center is loud and buzzing. But it's not a Jewish high holiday and there aren't any religious services -  it's just a regular night for the MetroWest Free Medical Program and the volunteers are busy making sure the night's patients each get time with doctors.Since November 2004, the free clinic has welcomed people in MetroWest without medical insurance to come and receive quality treatment.
